Business Brief -- Aluminum Co. of America:
   Research Staff to Eliminate
   54 Jobs in Budget-Cutting
Thirty-one of the 54 research jobs will be eliminated; the
others will be reassigned, dropping employment at
research-related jobs to 1,266.
   Alcoa reduced its U.S. employment by 300 in 1991, but its
overall employment grew to 65,600 from 63,700 because of
gains in Europe.